<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="339" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Both sexes</emphasis>
: clypeus narrower than LID (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4A</figureCitation>
); mid and hind femora without small spines set in pits apicodorsally. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Female</emphasis>
: thorax almost black (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3G</figureCitation>
); gena, in dorsal view, slightly thickened, roundly receding posteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3B</figureCitation>
); and lateral margin of pronotal dorsum, in dorsal view, concave, not narrowing anteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Male</emphasis>
: thorax dark rufous (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4I</figureCitation>
); frons, in profile, spherically convex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4I</figureCitation>
); placoids small, shorter than half of each flagellomere (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4E</figureCitation>
); SGP triangular with rounded apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4F</figureCitation>
); and inner margin of parapenial lobe finely and irregularly serrate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4G, H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="339" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Holotype</emphasis>
female.
</emphasis>
Length: Body 6.0 mm; forewing 5.9 mm. Body and legs black (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3D</figureCitation>
). Following dark rufous: palpi, clypeus, labrum, mandible, flagellum beneath, legs, and metasoma. Scape and pedicel beneath light brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3A</figureCitation>
). Wings translucent with brownish tint (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3F</figureCitation>
). Pubescence on pronotum posteriorly and mesonotum sericeous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
Head 1.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long. Vertex, in frontal view, almost transversely straight but slightly raised in ocellar area (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3A</figureCitation>
). Frons in lateral view strongly convex, but upper frons and vertex flattened (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3G</figureCitation>
), with frontal line very fine from antennal base to anterior ocellus. Antennocular line distinctly inclined from antennal base toward eye (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3B</figureCitation>
). MID 0.61 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
head width. UID:MID:LID = 8.1:10:7.5. POL:OOL = 1:0.86. Clypeus 2.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long; apical margin barely and arcuately emarginate. Gena, in profile, thin, 0.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
eye width (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3G</figureCitation>
). Scape:Fl1:Fl2 = 7.2:10:8.7; Fl1 4.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as thick, 0.78 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as UID.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
Pronotum gently and arcuately emarginate posteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3B</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum scarcely raised posterolaterally. Disc of scutellum not convex above level of mesoscutum. Metapostnotum 0.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as metanotum and depressed medially, with a few fine transverse striae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
Mid tibia with four spines externally and one spine internally; hind tibia with five or six spines externally and five spines internally (Fig. 
